Translate the following css to tailwind using the apply syntax.
expressions like var(--violet11) describe colors which can be translated to violet-11 in this case.
So "background-color: var(--violet4);" would for example translate to bg-violet-4
Selectors based on data attributes can also be translated using these two rules:
"[data-$x]" becomes "radix-$x:", "[data-state='$x']" becomes "radix-state-$x:" where $x can be any string.
merge selectors that use data-attributes into the corresponding class by using the two rules above. Here is an example on how to do this:

.MenubarTrigger[data-highlighted],
.MenubarTrigger[data-state='open'] {
  background-color: var(--violet4);
}

becomes

.MenubarTrigger {
    @apply radix-highlighted:bg-violet-4 radix-state-open:bg-violet-4
}

